MK Dons Rout Norwich in League Cup as Sunderland, QPR, Swansea Eliminated

-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 
2011-08-24T00:22:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/newly-promoted-premier-league-teams-sunderland-eliminated-from-league-cup.html
Newly promoted Norwich, Queens Park
Rangers and Swansea were among four Premier League teams to lose
in the second round of English soccer’s League Cup.  Norwich was routed 4-0 at home last night by MK Dons, who
lead  England ’s third-tier League One. QPR, bought last week by
AirAsia Bhd Chief Executive Officer  Tony Fernandes , was also
beaten at home, going down 2-0 to Rochdale.  Welsh club Swansea, which is playing in the Premier League
for the first time this season, lost 3-1 at fourth-tier
Shrewsbury. Established top-flight team Sunderland was beaten
1-0 at Brighton in a match that went to extra time. Craig
Mackail-Smith’s 96th-minute header gave Brighton the upset win.  Liverpool, Everton, Blackburn and Bolton play tonight,
while Newcastle visits Scunthorpe tomorrow. Teams playing in
 Europe ’s  Champions League  and Europa League enter England’s
second-tier cup competition in the third round.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  